The paper discusses a framework for Gaussian processes that enables the use of GPs on billions of datapoints, without requiring distributed inference or severe assumptions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GPs for computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS) applications, which further supports these sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of projections of the input space, which suggests that it may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
